fields.Title: INVENTORY / LIBRARY CARD
fields.Description: dead working class husband library card

fields.Title: A Folded Library Card: "The library card is folded into two..."
fields.Dialogue Text: The library card is folded into two and still slightly wet to the touch. The front side reads: "Central Jamrock Public Library Card. Issued to Billie MÃ©jean, expires July '53."

fields.Title: A Folded Library Card: "Something tells you you should give..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Something tells you you should give them a call.

fields.Title: A Folded Library Card: "You put the library card away."
fields.Dialogue Text: You put the library card away.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We should first decide what to do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We should first decide what to do with the body, before taking any other actions. Let's take another look at the body and talk things through."

fields.Title: Logic: "Billie is a unisex name. Could be t..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Billie is a unisex name. Could be the deceased *or* his family member?

fields.Title: A Folded Library Card: "Whoever owns this card is an avid r..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Whoever owns this card is an avid reader: you find a list of books written in blue pencil: 'Radiothriller', 'Stand a Little Less Between Me and the Sun'. The last one in the list is 'The Glinting Curve', by M. Thibault. A library stamp indicates that the book has been returned.

fields.Title: Logic: "You should first decide what to do..."
fields.Dialogue Text: You should first decide what to do with the corpse, before taking any further actions. Talk to the lieutenant about it.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good, we've examined the library c..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good, we've examined the library card -- that should be enough for our colleagues. Now we can call the station from my Kineema and hand over the case."

fields.Title: A Folded Library Card: ""If lost, please return the card to..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "If lost, please return the card to the library. Dial 005-02-55-211 or visit us at Meroe Street 78, Jamrock. Business hours: 09.00 to 18.00."

fields.Title: Reaction Speed: "Good idea. There was plenty of info..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Good idea. There was plenty of information here to go by.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""Good." He takes a note. "We should..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "Good." He takes a note. "We should give them a call from my Kineema, see if we can learn anything about Billie MÃ©jean."

fields.Title: Conceptualization: "Most of these titles seem to be in..."
fields.Dialogue Text: Most of these titles seem to be in the sci-fi genre. Some thrillers too.

fields.Title: Kim Kitsuragi: ""We already decided to let the stat..."
fields.Dialogue Text: "We already decided to let the station handle this case, so there's no need for us to call the library."
